Last night was my last time taking 15mg, tonight I'll take the first of seven 10mg doses. I don't know if such a small change will have noticeable effects but I'm going to try to check in every day anyway

My reason for switching is because the Lexapro isn't as effective as we hoped for depression nor anxiety. I've been feeling icky for a few months even after combining 15mg with therapy so this is our next step
This is my story. *Law & Order music*

I'm going to be switching to Venlafaxine 75mg which is a Serotonin-Norepinephrine Reuptake Inhibitor (SNRI).

My doctor told me to take 10mg once a day for a week, followed by 5mg for a week, then a two-day break before starting Venlafaxine.

I've been on Lexapro 15mg for over six months, before that I was on Lexapro 10mg for 2-3 years and before that, on and off from 2015 to around 2017.

It's a Selective Seratonin Reuptake Inhibitor (SSRI).

A thread of me coming off my current antidepressants and switching to new ones because it might be helpful to someone
